<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Chicken Note</div>
<div class="nbunit" id="udn106"> Bloom&apos;s observation of pigeons flocking about the Bank of Ireland building arises from B&eacute;rard&apos;s claim that Lestrygonia was a place filled with birds, particularly doves and pigeons, and also various pelagic species such as pelicans.  </div>
